snippet: Both Republicans and Democrats see the special election Tuesday as a potential harbinger, particularly with regards to the Affordable Care Act.
abstract: Both Republicans and Democrats see special election in Florida's 13th Congressional District as potential harbinger, testing potency of Affordable Care Act as an election issue; race between Republican David Jolly and Democrat Alex Sink kicks off high-stakes battle for control of Congress.
lead_paragraph: Both Republicans and Democrats see the special election Tuesday as a potential harbinger, particularly with regards to the Affordable Care Act.
